<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Long_and_short_scales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<p><a name="Current_UK_usage" id="Current_UK_usage"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Long_and_short_scales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: Current UK usage">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Current UK usage</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1974/dec/20/billion-definition#S5CV0883P0_19741220_CWA_439" class="external text" title="http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1974/dec/20/billion-definition#S5CV0883P0_19741220_CWA_439" rel="nofollow">"BILLION (DEFINITION)"</a>. Hansard<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1974/dec/20/billion-definition#S5CV0883P0_19741220_CWA_439" class="external free" title="http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1974/dec/20/billion-definition#S5CV0883P0_19741220_CWA_439" rel="nofollow">http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1974/dec/20/billion-definition#S5CV0883P0_19741220_CWA_439</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=BILLION+%28DEFINITION%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Hansard&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fhansard.millbanksystems.com%2Fwritten_answers%2F1974%2Fdec%2F20%2Fbillion-definition%23S5CV0883P0_19741220_CWA_439&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Long_and_short_scales"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> - the official Hansard report of 20 Dec 1974 when Harold Wilson defined 'Billion' for the UK Government.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/more_or_less/6625545.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/more_or_less/6625545.stm" rel="nofollow">"Who wants to be a trillionaire?"</a>. BBC<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/more_or_less/6625545.stm" class="external free" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/more_or_less/6625545.stm" rel="nofollow">http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/more_or_less/6625545.stm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Who+wants+to+be+a+trillionaire%3F&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=BBC&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Fprogrammes%2Fmore_or_less%2F6625545.stm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Long_and_short_scales"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> - a 2007 BBC page on actual common media usage of trillion.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.linguistlist.org/issues/7/7-451.html" class="external text" title="http://www.linguistlist.org/issues/7/7-451.html" rel="nofollow">"Linguist List 7.451"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.linguistlist.org/issues/7/7-451.html" class="external free" title="http://www.linguistlist.org/issues/7/7-451.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.linguistlist.org/issues/7/7-451.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Linguist+List+7.451&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.linguistlist.org%2Fissues%2F7%2F7-451.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Long_and_short_scales"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>- A 1996 email list message, comparing the two scales usage in different languages.</li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Traditional_UK_usage" id="Traditional_UK_usage"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Long_and_short_scales&amp;action=edit&amp;section=30" title="Edit section: Traditional UK usage">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Traditional UK usage</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.askoxford.com/asktheexperts/faq/aboutwords/billion?view=uk" class="external text" title="http://www.askoxford.com/asktheexperts/faq/aboutwords/billion?view=uk" rel="nofollow">"AskOxford: How many is a billion?"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.askoxford.com/asktheexperts/faq/aboutwords/billion?view=uk" class="external free" title="http://www.askoxford.com/asktheexperts/faq/aboutwords/billion?view=uk" rel="nofollow">http://www.askoxford.com/asktheexperts/faq/aboutwords/billion?view=uk</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=AskOxford%3A+How+many+is+a+billion%3F&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.askoxford.com%2Fasktheexperts%2Ffaq%2Faboutwords%2Fbillion%3Fview%3Duk&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Long_and_short_scales"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> - a traditional UK viewpoint.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.jimloy.com/math/billion.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.jimloy.com/math/billion.htm" rel="nofollow">"Million, Billion, Trillion ..."</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.jimloy.com/math/billion.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.jimloy.com/math/billion.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.jimloy.com/math/billion.htm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Million%2C+Billion%2C+Trillion+...&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jimloy.com%2Fmath%2Fbillion.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Long_and_short_scales"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> - a 1999 webpage comparing the long and short scale numbers, which only considers traditional UK numbering.</li>
</ul>


